Thought: 
  Congenital CMV infection is the most common congenital infection.
  Common clinical findings in patients with congenital CMV infection include a wide spectrum of manifestations, including:
    cerebral anomalies, namely microcephaly with or without ventriculomegaly;
    hepatosplenomegaly; 
    thrombocytopenia; 
    intrauterine growth restriction (IUGR); 
    petechiae; 
    lymphadenopathy; 
    chorioretinitis;
    and psychomotor developmental delay
  None of the listed options is commonly seen in a fetus with congenital CMV infection.
  Therefore, None of the Above seems to be the most appropriate answer.
Action: Answer("None of the Above")

Thought:
  Long-spaced collagen is a type of collagen that is composed of fibrils that are further apart than the fibrils in typical collagen;
  This type of collagen is found in the cornea of the eye;
  Therefore, the answer is B: Cornea.
Action: Answer("B")
